<main id="main" class="container narrow">
  <%- include('../partials/flash') %>
  <h1>Security &amp; Trust</h1>
  <p class="lead">Two kinds of "security" live on this page: real protections built into this application, and
  illustrative messaging that demonstrates what a real broker's page would say.</p>

  <h2>Real protections built into this app</h2>
  <ul class="check-list">
    <li>Passwords are hashed with bcrypt — we never store your actual password.</li>
    <li>Optional two-factor authentication (TOTP) using any authenticator app, with a QR code setup.</li>
    <li>Every page is protected against cross-site request forgery with a security token on every form.</li>
    <li>Login and money-moving pages are rate-limited to slow down automated abuse.</li>
    <li>A strict Content Security Policy blocks inline scripts entirely — every script on this site is a reviewable file.</li>
    <li>Session cookies are marked HTTP-only and secure, and your session is rotated every time you log in.</li>
    <li>You can view and revoke your active sessions, and review a full log of security-relevant activity, at any time.</li>
    <li>All database queries use parameterized statements, so there is no SQL-injection surface.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Illustrative messaging (not real)</h2>
  <p>The badges below appear on the homepage to demonstrate what a polished broker marketing site typically shows.
  They are <strong>not real claims</strong> about this application.</p>
  <ul class="check-list muted-list">
    <li>"Bank-grade encryption" — illustrative; this is a portfolio demo, not a bank.</li>
    <li>"Audited reserves" — illustrative; there are no reserves, because there are no real funds.</li>
    <li>"Regulated broker" — illustrative; USF Capital is not registered with or regulated by any financial authority.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="callout">
    <p>USF Capital does not custody funds, process real payments, or offer real investment products. Every balance
    shown anywhere on this site is generated by a mathematical simulation.</p>
  </div>
</main>
